just_use WingOracle.elm

# label: WORKHORSE (wings-oracle)
# role: derived data — which board stacks accept which dragged source, on which side

Pure helper that translates `BoardActions.findAllStackMerges` /
`tryStackMerge` / `tryHandMerge` results into the set of wings
to render during a drag.

## Exposed surface

- `type alias WingId = { target : CardStack, side : Side }` —
  content-based; target is the stack value itself, not a
  positional index.
- `wingsForStack : CardStack -> List CardStack -> List WingId`
  — enumerates wings for a board-stack drag source.
- `wingsForHandCard : HandCard -> List CardStack -> List WingId`
  — enumerates wings for a hand-card drag source.
- `wingBoardRect : WingId -> { left, top, width, height }` —
  pure board-frame rect the wing renders into. Used both by
  `Main.View.viewWingAt` at render time and by
  `Main.Gesture.floaterOverWing` for the hit-test.

## Calling convention

TARGET-first: `BoardActions.tryStackMerge target source side`
and `BoardActions.tryHandMerge target source side`. This makes
the target the "anchor" — the merged stack's position is
derived from the target, not the source — which matches the
drop-onto-target UX.

`side = Left` → source attaches to LEFT of target → wing
renders to the LEFT of target. Same for Right. No flipping,
no inversion. See memory `feedback_skill_as_three_factors`-
adjacent: keep LEFT and RIGHT as two distinct cases.

## Why two functions instead of one polymorphic

Stack-source and hand-source paths are deliberately kept as
two separate functions; they are two similar things, not one
parameterized thing. Mirrors Steve's "strong concept of LEFT
and RIGHT" rule applied to source type.

## Pointers

- Consumers: `Main.Gesture.startBoardCardDrag` /
  `startHandDrag` (build the wings list at drag start);
  `Main.Gesture.floaterOverWing` (hit-test on MouseMove);
  `Main.View.viewWingAt` (render).
- Depends on: `BoardActions.tryStackMerge` /
  `BoardActions.tryHandMerge` (faithful TS port).
- Tests: `tests/Game/WingOracleTest.elm` covers wingsForStack
  correctness + wingBoardRect math.
